main event: A radar object was sighted over Sioux City, Iowa in 1956.
interesting points: The object was detected on radar and was described as being the size of an orange at ground level.
The object moved from west to east and gained altitude.
The sighting lasted for 1 minute and 31 seconds.
The report concludes that the sighting was likely a meteor.
Additional details about the object's appearance and behavior are provided in the report.
